how to make cheese puffs easy short recipe please cheese puffs cup milk pound stick unsalted butter teaspoon kosher salt teaspoon freshly ground black pepper pinch nutmeg cup all purpose flour extra large eggs cup grated gruyere plus extra for sprinkling cup freshly grated parmesan egg beaten with teaspoon water for egg wash preheat the oven to f line baking sheets with parchment paper in a saucepan heat the milk butter salt pepper and nutmeg over medium heat until scalded add the flour all at once and beat it vigorously with a wooden spoon until the mixture comes together cook stirring constantly over low heat for minutes the flour will begin to coat the bottom of the pan dump the hot mixture into the bowl of a food processor fitted with the steel blade immediately add the eggs gruyere and parmesan and pulse until the eggs are incorporated and the dough is smooth and thick spoon the mixture into a pastry bag fitted with a large plain round tip pipe in mounds inches wide and inch high onto the baking sheets with a wet finger lightly press down the swirl at the top of each puff you can also use spoons to scoop out the mixture and shape the puffs with damp fingers brush the top of each puff lightly with egg wash and sprinkle with a pinch of gruyere bake for minutes or until golden brown outside but still soft inside ina garten puff pastry cheese straws sheets box frozen puff pastry such as pepperidge farm defrosted overnight in the refrigerator flour for dusting extra large egg tablespoon water cup freshly grated parmesan cup finely grated gruy re cheese teaspoon minced fresh thyme leaves teaspoon kosher salt freshly ground black pepper preheat the oven to f roll out each sheet of puff pastry on a lightly floured board until it is by inches beat the egg with tablespoon of water and brush the surface of the pastry sprinkle each sheet evenly with cup of the parmesan cup of the gruy re teaspoon of the thyme teaspoon of the salt and some pepper with the rolling pin lightly press the flavorings into the puff pastry cut each sheet crosswise with a floured knife or pizza wheel into or strips twist each strip and lay on baking sheets lined with parchment paper bake for to minutes or until lightly browned and puffed turn each straw and bake for another minutes don't over bake or the cheese will burn cool and serve at room temperature ina garten Bengali cuisine Pancake Rice pudding Cooking weights and measures Cookware and bakeware Ice cream Drill bit Recipe Halva Knife Textile manufacturing Casting Baklava Tortilla Sushi Kraft Dinner In-N-Out Burger Pottery Welding Cuisine of Singapore Butter Ramen Curry Carbon dioxide Microwave oven Potato Plastic Cincinnati chili Wok Chocolate Pasta Thermal power station Kosher foods Chowder Dim sum Vinegar Turkish coffee Cajun cuisine Tobacco Soul food Mattress Milk Comanche D__ner kebab Risotto Korean cuisine Chicago-style pizza Potato pancakes Cooking Fondue Violin Gumbo Dosa Baked Alaska Custard Glass Pop-Tarts Flax Nutmeg Roman eating and drinking Roast beef Polish cuisine Roux Glacier Steel Genericized trademark Spoon Yoghurt 